WEBVTT

00:18.800 --> 00:21.600
CHAPTER XIX.

00:22.740 --> 00:24.100
THE BURDEN OF EGYPT

00:24.100 --> 00:30.540
Behold, the LORD writeth upon a swift cloud, and shall come into Egypt, and the idols

00:30.540 --> 00:35.820
of Egypt shall be moved at his presence, and the heart of Egypt shall melt in the midst

00:35.820 --> 00:36.340
of it.

00:37.000 --> 00:42.340
And I will set the Egyptians against the Egyptians, and they shall fight every one against his

00:42.340 --> 00:47.840
brother, and every one against his neighbor, city against city, and kingdom against kingdom.

00:48.500 --> 00:53.580
And the spirit of Egypt shall fail in the midst thereof, and I will destroy the council

00:53.580 --> 00:58.040
thereof, and they shall seek to the idols, and to the charmers, and to them that have

00:58.040 --> 01:00.020
familiar spirits, and to the wizards.

01:00.840 --> 01:06.440
And the Egyptians will I give over into the hand of a cruel LORD, and a fierce king shall

01:06.440 --> 01:09.440
rule over them, said the LORD, the LORD of hosts.

01:10.340 --> 01:15.340
And the waters shall fail from the sea, and the river shall be wasted and dried up.

01:16.260 --> 01:21.760
And they shall turn the rivers far away, and the brooks of defense shall be emptied and

01:21.760 --> 01:22.380
dried up.

01:22.700 --> 01:24.780
The reeds and flags shall wither.

01:25.440 --> 01:30.300
The paper reeds by the brooks, by the mouth of the brooks, and everything sewn by the

01:30.300 --> 01:33.600
brooks, shall wither, be driven away, and be no more.

01:34.540 --> 01:40.480
The fishers also shall mourn, and all they that cast ankle into the brooks shall lament,

01:40.960 --> 01:43.980
and they that spread nets upon the waters shall languish.

01:44.640 --> 01:50.740
Moreover, they that work in fine flax, and they that weave networks, shall be confounded,

01:51.020 --> 01:57.000
and they shall be broken in the purposes thereof, all that make sluices and ponds for fish.

01:58.440 --> 02:00.880
Surely the princes of Zoan are fools.

02:01.260 --> 02:05.140
The counsel of the wise counselors of Pharaoh is become brutish.

02:05.400 --> 02:10.620
How say ye unto Pharaoh, I am the son of the wise, the son of ancient kings.

02:11.840 --> 02:12.860
Where are they?

02:13.260 --> 02:14.660
Where are thy wise men?

02:15.020 --> 02:20.920
And let them tell thee now, and let them know what the Lord of hosts hath purposed upon

02:20.920 --> 02:21.420
Egypt.

02:22.320 --> 02:24.700
The princes of Zoan are become fools.

02:25.200 --> 02:27.320
The princes of Noph are deceived.

02:27.740 --> 02:33.960
They have also seduced Egypt, even they that are the stay of the tribes thereof.

02:35.460 --> 02:40.420
The Lord hath mingled a perverse spirit in the midst thereof, and they have caused Egypt

02:40.420 --> 02:44.960
to err in every work thereof, as a drunken man staggereth in his vomit.

02:46.300 --> 02:51.600
Neither shall there be any work for Egypt, which the head or tail, branch or rush may

02:51.600 --> 02:52.040
do.

02:52.560 --> 02:57.780
In that day shall Egypt be like unto women, and it shall be afraid and feared because

02:57.780 --> 03:02.000
of the shaking of the hand of the Lord of hosts, which he shaketh over it.

03:02.700 --> 03:08.340
And the land of Judah shall be a terror unto Egypt, every one that maketh mention thereof

03:08.340 --> 03:13.220
shall be afraid in himself because of the counsel of the Lord of hosts, which he hath

03:13.220 --> 03:14.420
determined against it.

03:15.560 --> 03:21.200
In that day shall five cities in the land of Egypt speak the language of Canaan, and

03:21.200 --> 03:25.280
swear to the Lord of hosts, one shall be called the city of destruction.

03:26.100 --> 03:31.400
In that day shall there be an altar to the Lord in the midst of the land of Egypt, and

03:31.400 --> 03:33.540
a pillar at the border thereof to the Lord.

03:33.540 --> 03:38.980
And it shall be for a sign and for a witness unto the Lord of hosts in the land of Egypt,

03:39.460 --> 03:44.680
for they shall cry unto the Lord because of the oppressors, and he shall send them a Savior

03:44.680 --> 03:47.820
and a great one, and he shall deliver them.

03:48.440 --> 03:52.980
And the Lord shall be known to Egypt, and the Egyptians shall know the Lord in that

03:52.980 --> 03:58.380
day, and shall do sacrifice and oblation, yea, they shall vow a vow unto the Lord and

03:58.380 --> 03:59.200
perform it.

03:59.970 --> 04:05.680
And the Lord shall smite Egypt, he shall smite and heal it, and they shall return even to

04:05.680 --> 04:09.340
the Lord, and he shall be entreated of them, and shall heal them.

04:10.180 --> 04:15.920
In that day shall there be a highway out of Egypt to Syria, and the Assyrians shall come

04:15.920 --> 04:21.600
into Egypt and the Egyptians into Assyria, and the Egyptians shall serve with the Assyrians.

04:22.540 --> 04:27.890
In that day shall Israel be the third with Egypt and with Assyria, even a blessing in

04:27.890 --> 04:33.670
the midst of the land, whom the Lord of hosts shall bless, saying, Blessed be Egypt, my

04:33.670 --> 04:37.990
people, and Assyria, the work of my hands, and Israel, mine inheritance.

04:40.090 --> 04:41.210
Chapter 20

04:41.990 --> 04:47.990
In the year that Tartan came unto Ashdod, when Sargon the king of Assyria sent him,

04:48.330 --> 04:56.830
and fought against Ashdod and took it, at the same time spake the Lord by Isaiah the

04:56.830 --> 05:02.290
black cloth from off thy loins, and put off thy shoe from thy foot, and he did so, walking

05:02.290 --> 05:03.470
naked and barefoot.

05:04.090 --> 05:10.250
And the Lord said, Like as my servant Isaiah hath walked naked and barefoot three years,

05:10.650 --> 05:16.870
for a sign and wonder upon Egypt and upon Ethiopia, so shall the king of Assyria lead

05:16.870 --> 05:23.050
away the Egyptian prisoners and the Ethiopians captives, young and old, naked and barefoot,

05:23.050 --> 05:26.270
even with their buttocks uncovered, to the shame of Egypt.

05:27.350 --> 05:32.990
They shall be afraid, and ashamed of Ethiopia their expectation, and of Egypt their glory.

05:33.810 --> 05:39.690
And the inhabitant of this isle shall say in that day, Behold, such is our expectation,

05:40.290 --> 05:45.530
whither we flee for help to be delivered from the king of Assyria, and how shall we escape?

05:47.670 --> 05:48.790
Chapter 21

05:49.270 --> 05:51.350
The Burden of the Desert of the Sea

05:51.750 --> 05:56.210
As whirlwinds in the south pass through, so it cometh from the desert from a terrible

05:56.210 --> 05:56.590
land.

05:57.250 --> 06:02.430
A grievous vision is declared unto me, the treacherous dealer dealeth treacherously,

06:02.730 --> 06:04.170
and the spoiler spoileth.

06:04.750 --> 06:10.190
Go up, O Elam, besiege, O Media, all the sign thereof have I made to cease.

06:11.010 --> 06:16.630
Therefore are my loins filled with pain, pangs have taken hold upon me, as the pangs of a

06:16.630 --> 06:17.670
woman that travelleth.

06:18.030 --> 06:22.470
I was bowed down at the hearing of it, I was dismayed at the seeing of it.

06:23.150 --> 06:28.050
My heart panted, fearfulness affrightened me, the night of my pleasure hath he turned

06:28.050 --> 06:29.490
to do fear unto me.

06:29.890 --> 06:36.930
Prepare the table, watch in the watch-tower, eat, drink, arise ye princes, and anoint the

06:36.930 --> 06:37.290
shield.

06:38.470 --> 06:44.830
For thus hath the Lord said unto me, Go, set a watchman, let him declare what he seeth.

06:45.450 --> 06:51.950
And he saw a chariot with a couple of horsemen, a chariot of asses, and a chariot of camels,

06:52.170 --> 06:54.530
and he hearkened diligently with much heed.

06:55.090 --> 07:01.590
And he cried, A lion, my lord, I stand continually upon the watch-tower in the day-time, and

07:01.590 --> 07:04.490
I am set in my ward whole nights.

07:05.510 --> 07:09.870
And behold, here cometh a chariot of men with a couple of horsemen.

07:09.870 --> 07:15.590
And he answered and said, Babylon is fallen, is fallen, and all the graven images of her

07:15.590 --> 07:17.810
gods he hath broken unto the ground.

07:19.030 --> 07:24.770
O my threshing and the corn of my floor, that which I have heard of the Lord of hosts, the

07:24.770 --> 07:27.010
God of Israel, have I declared unto you.

07:28.510 --> 07:29.630
The burden of Duma.

07:30.390 --> 07:36.350
He calleth to me out of seer, Watchman, what of the night, watchman, what of the night?

07:36.890 --> 07:40.550
The watchman said, The morning cometh, and also the night.

07:40.990 --> 07:44.450
If ye will inquire, inquire ye, return, come.

07:45.690 --> 07:46.890
The burden upon Arabia.

07:47.370 --> 07:52.310
In the forest in Arabia shall ye lodge, O ye travelling companies of Dedanim.

07:53.010 --> 07:56.890
The inhabitants of the land of Tima brought water to him that was thirsty.

07:57.330 --> 07:59.690
They prevented with their bread him that fled.

08:00.550 --> 08:05.410
For they fled from the swords, from the drawn swords, and from the bent bow, and from the

08:05.410 --> 08:06.830
grievousness of war.

08:07.410 --> 08:13.190
For thus hath the Lord said unto me, Within a year, according to the years of an hireling,

08:13.550 --> 08:15.730
and all the glory of Keter shall fail.

08:16.210 --> 08:21.710
And the residue of the number of archers, the mighty men of the children of Keter, shall

08:21.710 --> 08:25.530
be diminished, for the Lord God of Israel hath spoken it.

